        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: C-terminally GFP-tagged ATG-9 colocalizes with the synaptic vesicle associated protein RAB-3 in axons.. Experimental description: All worms were cultivated at 20°C on NGM plates seeded with OP50 E. coli. As a wild type reference strain, we utilized N2 Bristol worms." ;
